
This directory contains the Postscript source files for the
transparency masters for the Joy of C.  There is one Postscript
file for each of the 22 chapters in the text.  These files are
organized in the obvious way: chap01.ps contains the masters
for Chapter 1, chap02.ps contains the masters for Chapter 2,
and so on.

Each file is between 20-40 pages, depending on the length of
the chapter.  

We are always interested in new programming examples and figures that
instructors find useful for their classes.  If you create anything
for your class that you think would be generally useful, please 
send mail describing them to alex@wiliki.eng.hawaii.edu.  If
they're done in LaTeX, we'll be glad to do the work of tuning them
to our slide format and making them generally available in future
releases of these transparency masters.  



PUBLISHER-REQUIRED NASTY COPYRIGHT NOTICE:

These transparency masters are copyrighted by John Wiley & Sons,
1993.  They are made available to instructors for the express
purpose of aiding their teaching of any course that uses the
Joy of C as a class textbook.   
